prologue_2efffb1a		"But, most importantly, a house doesn't have the memory of a deceased loved one lingering in all of the things scattered around the cramped space."	game/script.rpy	39		prologue_2efffb1a
prologue_951f0d6e		"Not in the always tidy hamper, or the uncluttered top shelf of the wall unit. Not even in the almost empty refrigerator."	game/script.rpy	40		prologue_951f0d6e
prologue_b1e73afe		"My two bedroom walk up certainly isn't a house, but it is a home. A home filled with painful memories that I can no longer stomach. That's why I'm leaving. "	game/script.rpy	44		prologue_b1e73afe
prologue_c35355dd		"Not for good, that would kill my beautiful mother's taped together smile."	game/script.rpy	48		prologue_c35355dd
prologue_bd2d02bb		"But, I'll leave until all of the holiday cheer in the streets of New York City is gone. Until I no longer have to watch my mother wrap a gift and label it ""To Craig, from Santa."""	game/script.rpy	49		prologue_bd2d02bb
